0x00000000.description: Control register for enabling FEC functions.
0x00000000.name: EthRsFecControl

0x00000008.description: Counts number of corrected FEC codewords lower 16-bits; None roll-over when upper 16-bits are 0xffff.
0x00000008.name: EthRsFecCcwLo

0x0000000c.description: Counts number of corrected FEC codewords upper 16-bits; Clears on read; None roll-over.
0x0000000c.name: EthRsFecCcwHi

0x00000010.description: Counts number of uncorrected FEC codewords lower 16-bits; None roll-over when upper 16-bits are 0xffff.
0x00000010.name: EthRsFecNccwLo

0x00000014.description: Counts number of uncorrected FEC codewords upper 16-bits; Clears on read; None roll-over.
0x00000014.name: EthRsFecNccwHi

0x00000018.description: FEC alignment status and lane mappings.
0x00000018.name: EthRsFecLanemap

0x00000028.description: Counts number of (corrected) 10-bit symbol errors found in lane 0; None roll-over when upper 16-bits are 0xffff.
0x00000028.name: EthRsFecSymblerr0Lo

0x0000002c.description: Upper 16-bit of counter (with above register); Clears on read; None roll-over.
0x0000002c.name: EthRsFecSymblerr0Hi

0x00000030.description: Counts number of (corrected) 10-bit symbol errors found in lane 1; None roll-over when upper 16-bits are 0xffff.
0x00000030.name: EthRsFecSymblerr1Lo

0x00000034.description: Upper 16-bit of counter (with above register); Clears on read; None roll-over.
0x00000034.name: EthRsFecSymblerr1Hi

0x00000038.description: Counts number of (corrected) 10-bit symbol errors found in lane 2; None roll-over when upper 16-bits are 0xffff.
0x00000038.name: EthRsFecSymblerr2Lo

0x0000003c.description: Upper 16-bit of counter (with above register); Clears on read; None roll-over.
0x0000003c.name: EthRsFecSymblerr2Hi

0x00000040.description: Counts number of (corrected) 10-bit symbol errors found in lane 3; None roll-over when upper 16-bits are 0xffff.
0x00000040.name: EthRsFecSymblerr3Lo

0x00000044.description: Upper 16 bit of counter (with above register); Clears on read; None roll-over.
0x00000044.name: EthRsFecSymblerr3Hi

0x00000200.description: Additional control to enable RS-FEC operation.
0x00000200.name: EthRsFecVendorControl

0x00000204.description: Implementation specific information that may be useful for debugging link problems; Clears on read.
0x00000204.name: EthRsFecVendorInfo1

0x00000208.description: Implementation specific status information; Clears on read.
0x00000208.name: EthRsFecVendorInfo2

0x0000020c.description: A version information taken from package file parameter FEC91_DEV_VERSION.
0x0000020c.name: EthRsFecVendorRevision

0x00000210.description: Bits 7:0; Must be written with the 8-bit value of 0x57 to enable RS-FEC transmit test error injection capability.
0x00000210.name: EthRsFecVendorTxTestKey

0x00000214.description: Bits 15:0. One bit per 10-bit Symbol; Each bit is applied to corresponding 10B symbol after FEC encoding.
0x00000214.name: EthRsFecVendorTxTestsymbols

0x00000218.description: Bits 9:0; A 10-bit value which XORed with a 10B symbol FEC encoder to manipulate transmitted datastream.
0x00000218.name: EthRsFecVendorTxTestPattern

0x0000021c.description: Enable register to control the triggers with the error insertion; Bit 0 clears on operation complete.
0x0000021c.name: EthRsFecVendorTxTesttrigger

fields.description: Counts number of corrected FEC codewords upper 16-bits; None roll-over; Clears when read.
fields.name: EthCounterHi

fields.description: Counts number of corrected FEC codewords lower 16-bits; Must be read before upper 16-bits; None roll-over when upper 16-bits are 0xffff
fields.name: EthCounter

fields.description: When 1, configure the FEC decoder to not indicate errors to the PCS layer; When  0, the FEC decoder indicates errors to the PCS layer.
fields.name: EthBypassErrorIndication

fields.description: When 1, bypass the decoder's correction function for reduced latency; When  0, normal FEC operation.
fields.name: EthBypassCorrection

fields.description: FEC lane mapped to PMA lane 3.
fields.name: EthPmaLane3

fields.description: FEC lane mapped to PMA lane 2.
fields.name: EthPmaLane2

fields.description: FEC lane mapped to PMA lane 1.
fields.name: EthPmaLane1

fields.description: FEC lane mapped to PMA lane 0.
fields.name: EthPmaLane0

fields.description: Counts number of uncorrected FEC codewords upper 16-bits; None roll-over; Clears when read.
fields.name: EthCounterHi

fields.description: Counts number of uncorrected FEC codewords lower 16-bits; Must be read before upper 16-bits; None roll-over when upper 16-bits are 0xffff
fields.name: EthCounter

fields.description: Always 1.
fields.name: EthPcsAlignStatus

fields.description: Indicates, when 1 that the RS-FEC receiver has locked on incoming data and deskew completed.
fields.name: EthFecAlignStatus

fields.description: RS-FEC receive lane locked and aligned; One bit per lane: Bit 8 = lane 0, Bit 9 = lane 1, Bit 10= lane 2, Bit 11 = lane 3.
fields.name: EthAmpsLock

fields.description: Asserts when error indication bypass is enabled and high symbol error rate is found;  Clear on read.
fields.name: EthHighSer

fields.description: Indicates the ability to disable error propagation to the PCS layer.
fields.name: EthBypassIndication

fields.description: Indicates existence of the receive correction bypass option; The bypass function allows a reduced latency operation.
fields.name: EthBypassCorrection

fields.description: Upper 16-bits of the 32-bit Symbol error counter for lane 0; Clears on read; None roll-over.
fields.name: EthSymbolErrorHi

fields.description: Counts number of (corrected) 10-bit symbol errors found in lane 0 for correctable codewords only; Lower 16-bit of counter; Must be read first; None roll-over when upper word is 0xffff.
fields.name: EthSymbolErrors

fields.description: Upper 16-bits of the 32-bit Symbol error counter for lane 1; Clears on read; None roll-over.
fields.name: EthSymbolErrorHi

fields.description: Counts number of (corrected) 10-bit symbol errors found in lane 1 for correctable codewords only; Lower 16-bit of counter; Must be read first; None roll-over when upper word is 0xffff.
fields.name: EthSymbolErrors

fields.description: Upper 16-bits of the 32-bit Symbol error counter for lane 2; Clears on read; None roll-over.
fields.name: EthSymbolErrorHi

fields.description: Counts number of (corrected) 10-bit symbol errors found in lane 2 for correctable codewords only; Lower 16-bit of counter; Must be read first; None roll-over when upper word is 0xffff.
fields.name: EthSymbolErrors

fields.description: Upper 16-bits of the 32-bit Symbol error counter for lane 3; Clears on read; None roll-over.
fields.name: EthSymbolErrorHi

fields.description: Counts number of (corrected) 10-bit symbol errors found in lane 3 for correctable codewords only; Lower 16-bit of counter; Must be read first; None roll-over when upper word is 0xffff.
fields.name: EthSymbolErrors

fields.description: Indicates the operatyional outcome of the (above) enable bit control; When 1 = FEC enabled and 0 = disabled.
fields.name: EthRsFecStatus

fields.description: When 1, enable RSFEC datapath instead PCS MLD;  When 0, use normal PCS MLD datapath (default).
fields.name: EthRsFecEnable

fields.description: Real-time indication from FEC deskew FIFO per lane; bit 12 = lane 0 upto bit 15 = lane3.
fields.name: EthDeskewEmpty

fields.description: FEC alignment status; Latched high; Sets on read.
fields.name: EthFecAlignStatusLl

fields.description: TX datapath 4x66 input fifo overflow fatal error; Latched high; Clear on read.
fields.name: EthTxDpOverflow

fields.description: RX datapath 4x66 pacing fifo overflow fatal error; Latched high; Clear on read.
fields.name: EthRxDpOverflow

fields.description: TX datapath (sync) reset occured; Latched high; Clear on read.
fields.name: EthTxDatapathRestart

fields.description: RX datapath (sync) reset occured; Latched high; Clear on read.
fields.name: EthRxDatapathRestart

fields.description: The marker_check function (PCS sublayer) caused an alignment restart to the FEC; Latched high; Clear on read.
fields.name: EthMarkerCheckRestart

fields.description: FEC alignment status; Latched high; Clear on read.
fields.name: EthFecAlignStatusLh

fields.description: Per PMA lane FEC synchronization status; Bit 0=lane 0 up to Bit 3 = lane 3; Latched high; Clear on read.
fields.name: EthAmpsLock

fields.description: Per PMA lane FEC synchronization status; Realtime updates;  Bit  0 = lane 0 upto bit 3 = lane 3; Clears on read;
fields.name: EthAmpsLock

fields.description: A version information taken from package file parameter FEC91_DEV_VERSION.
fields.name: EthRevision

fields.description: Bits 7:0; Must be written with 8-bit value 0x57 to enable RS-FEC transmit test error injection capability.
fields.name: EthTestKey

fields.description: If the bit is set the 10B symbol is replaced by the pattern instead using XOR.
fields.name: EthOverwrite

fields.description: A 10-bit value which will be XORed with a 10B symbol after the FEC encoder to manipulate the transmitted datastream.
fields.name: EthTestPattern

fields.description: Bits 15:0. One bit per 10-bit Symbol; When a bit is 1 the test pattern is applied to the corresponding 10B symbol after the FEC encoding.
fields.name: EthTestSymbols

fields.description: For bit 0 only, when written with 1 triggers the error insertion (on one word of 16 symbols); This bit clears automatically.
fields.name: EthTestTrigger
